        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 6:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". As easily as the moth-grub, working unseen, destroys ‘goodly raiment’ (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 27:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), so easily does God’s chastisement destroy a man’s ‘goodliness,’ the bodily strength and beauty which make him attractive (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 53:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). It is God’s consuming ‘hand’ which is compared to the ‘moth’ (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hosea 5:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); not, as the A.V. might seem to imply, the ephemeral duration of man’s goodliness. Cp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 13:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
